-- HK stocks slip ahead of China data, Chinese shares have best week in 6 
-- By Donny Kwok
-- Fri Sep 05, 2014 04:07AM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, Sept 5 (Reuters) - Hong Kong shares finished slightly lower on Friday as investors locked in gains ahead of a new round of Chinese economic data and a market holiday early next week.

The Hang Seng Index <.HSI> closed down 0.2 percent at 25,240.15. The China Enterprises Index <.HSCE> of the leading offshore Chinese listings in Hong Kong was down 0.2 percent. On the week, the Hang Seng Index added 2.0 percent and the HSCE rose 3.7 percent in its best week in six. Chinese markets will be shut on Monday for the Mid-Autumn Festival, while Hong Kong will be closed on Tuesday for the holiday.